.TH THEMECTL-APPLY 1 "2024" "themectl" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
themectl apply \- apply a theme to all applications
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B themectl apply
\fITHEME\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Apply a theme to all detected applications. \fBthemectl\fR will automatically
detect configuration file locations and create backups before modifying files.
.PP
The theme name should not include the .toml extension.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-config-dir \fIPATH\fR
Override the default config directory (~/.config)
.TP
.BR \-\-apps \fIAPPS\fR
Apply to specific applications only (comma-separated list)
.TP
.BR \-\-variant \fIVARIANT\fR
Apply a specific variant (dark/light)
.SH EXAMPLES
Apply a theme to all applications:
.RS
.PP
themectl apply gruvbox-dark
.RE
.PP
Apply theme to specific applications:
.RS
.PP
themectl apply gruvbox-dark --apps kitty,waybar,neovim
.RE
.PP
Apply a light variant:
.RS
.PP
themectl apply gruvbox --variant light
.RE
.PP
Preview changes without applying:
.RS
.PP
themectl apply gruvbox-dark --dry-run
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR themectl (1),
.BR themectl-preview (1)
